  "Not only that, I found another paper suggesting that inactivity must be to blame because people in the UK are collectively eating fewer calories than they used to.[22]",
  "If people are eating fewer calories but still gaining weight then they must be far more inactive than before.",
  "This paper was by Christopher Snowdon, the journalist (and ‘head of lifestyle economics’) at the Institute for Economic Affairs (who also derided the very idea of UPF in Chapter 2).",
